summary: An ordinance fixing the rate of taxes to be levied and levying the taxes upon all taxable property, both real and personal, in the City of Seattle, in order to raise sufficient revenue to carry on the different departments and activities of the Municipal Government of the City of Seattle, including the interest to accrue on bonded debt and redemption of bonds falling due during the ensuing fiscal year, to-wit: for the year beginning on the first day of January, 1927 and ending on the 31st day of December 1927.
